BEGIN PROMPT

Task:
Convert the following raw transcript or notes into a structured meeting summary for the HCPT Overlay Project.
Follow the exact structure and narrative depth of the Maui County Wastewater Coordination Summary (October 2025) https://github.com/cshuler/WW_Overlay_2024/blob/main/Document_Archive/Meeting_Notes/County_Meetings_Maui/Maui_Oct_15_2025_Summary_Narratives_Details_AI.pdf.

Output Format:

Date/Context

Describe the meeting date, setting, participants (with affiliations), and any relevant legislative or project context.

Purpose

State the purpose of the meeting:

coordination

feedback collection

data alignment

terminology review

preparation for legislative briefing
(or whatever is appropriate based on the transcript)

Key Narratives and Findings
1. Project Scope & Goals

Summarize:

Act 125 / 132 / 217 context

HCPT project mandate

deadlines, expected deliverables

high-level goals expressed in the meeting

importance for county or state policy

2. Data Coordination

Document:

cesspool counts, cluster logic (≥50 in ⅛ mile)

proximity thresholds

Carollo polygons and cost data

updates/corrections needed

any specific GIS or shapefile issues

what data each side agreed to share

3. Terminology & Communication

Capture discussion of terms such as:

feasible

technically possible

proximal

under study

public messaging and disclaimers

county concerns about misinterpretation

4. County / Project-Specific Details

Produce a table in this format:

Area / Project	Status / Notes	Cost / Constraints
Example	Example	Example

Include:

whether reclassification recommendations came from the County, UH team, or both

disagreements or resistance

infrastructure context

pump stations, elevation barriers, DHHL boundaries

economic feasibility information

5. Cross-County / Coordination Issues

Summarize any broader statewide issues mentioned, such as:

data sharing differences among counties

Carollo alignment challenges

political sensitivities

timing of Carollo data release

legislative expectations

6. Next Actions

List specific follow-up tasks for:

UH WRRC team

County staff

Carollo

legislators (if relevant)

Use clear bullet points.

Core Takeaways

Write a concise synthesis (3–5 sentences) addressing:

the most important conclusions

what changed

where alignment was achieved

where disagreements remain

implications for statewide mapping and reporting

Appendix Note

Include this statement at the end:

“Meeting notes and summary from the October 17 meeting will be amended here or may be compiled as a separate document and referenced in future versions.”

END PROMPT
